casebody.data:
NATIONSTAR MORTGAGE LLC d/b/a Champion Mortgage Company, Respondent,
v.
Larry D. WILLS, Appellant. WD 81498 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. ORDER FILED: December 18, 2018 Nancy M. Wilson, Overland Park, KS, Attorney for Respondent. Larry D. Willis, Kansas City, MO, Appellant, pro se. Before Division Two: Alok Ahuja, Presiding Judge, and Thomas H. Newton and Mark D. Pfeiffer, Judges

Order

Per Curiam:

Mr. Larry D. Wills appeals from the judgment of the Circuit Court of Jackson County, Missouri, in favor of Nationstar Mortgage LLC, d/b/a Champion Mortgage Company, and against Larry Wills, the Heirs at Law of Lela M. Wills, and tenants/occupants John Doe and Mary Doe. The judgment granted Nationstar possession of unlawfully detained premises after foreclosure. Because a published opinion would have no precedential value, a memorandum of law has been provided to the parties. The judgment is affirmed. Rule 84.16(b).
